fwprop.note:
This procedure processes the Time-Based Activities (TBAs) in the Time-Based Schedule (TBS)
The procedure is started when the TBS function is enabled and stopped when it is disabled. The host
application is responsible for periodically executing it. At every call, this procedure processes the TBAs
whose release time is in the past starting from the TBA pointed at by firstTba

fwprop.entryDesc:
Extract InCommand component
from TBA pointed at by firstTba

Select InManager
where to load InCommand

Run Packet Acceptance Failure
Procedure to generate (1,2) report
with VER_ACC_FAIL

Run Packet Acceptance Failure
Procedure to generate (1,2) report
with VER_LD_FAIL

Run Command Verification
Acceptance Success Procedure
to generate (1,1) for InCommand

Return InCommand component
to InFaactor with operation Release

fwprop.note:
Each TBA has attributes nextTba and prevTba which point to the 
TBA with the next and the previous release time. When a TBA is 
removed from the TBS, the nextTba and prevTba of its nearby TBAs
are updated to maintainthe integrity of the TBS. This is done in node N12.
firstTba is an attribute of the TBS which points to the  TBA with earliest release time
Same adaptation point as in the InLoader

fwprop.entryDesc:
Clear firstTba slot in TBS by setting its
release time to zero; Update nextTba and prevTba
attributes of nearby TBAs; Update number of TBAs 
in sub-schedule and group of firstTba-th TBA; Update
number of non=empty sub-schedules and groups;
Update firstTba to point to the next TBA in TBS

fwprop.note:
A TBA is enabled if both its group
and its sub-schedule  are enabled

fwprop.guardDesc:
InCommand is not
in state CONFIGURED

Load operation is
successful and InCommand
does not requires acknowledgement
of successful acceptance
TBA pointed at by firstTba is disabled

Current time is smaller
than release time of
firstTba-th TBA in TBS
